title: Experimental and theoretical insights into benzene-1,4-dicarboxylic acid based Co-MOFs: an anodic material for expedient battery-supercapacitor hybrids
content:
Sustainable Energy Fuels, 2024, Advance Article
DOI: 10.1039/D4SE00590B, Paper
Junaid Khan, Anique Ahmed, Muhammad Imran Saleem, Abdullah A. Al-Kahtani
A Co-MOF assembled hybrid supercapacitor exhibits outstanding specific energy and power (60.07 W h kg−1 and 850 W kg−1) with 80.01% diffusive and 76.72% capacitive contribution at 3 and 100 mV s−1, respectively.
